init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A voice on the other end tells you to meet "him" in an hour at the Old Executive Office Building.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Not wanting to waste time, you walk from the landing strip to the Old Executive Office Building.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Come with us, Barack," says Ike, to which you follow up a flight of stairs to a door marked "EXECUTIVE".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: What is the "Important Job" you must perform.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: sits down, and begins to explain the situation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Barack, this is the real thing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: but that there are many different worlds, and they all have their own challenges, and to be the best in the universe, you must be tested.
